WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.000
Fozzie: ALL RIGHT,

00:02.000 --> 00:05.166
MISS PIGGY'S GONNA BE COMING OUT
IN A COUPLE OF MINUTES.

00:05.166 --> 00:06.875
Statler: OH. WHATEVER.
YEAH!

00:06.875 --> 00:07.958
Waldorf: YEAH.
YEAH!

00:07.958 --> 00:10.333
SO, BEFORE WE START
THE SHOW,

00:10.333 --> 00:12.125
HOW ABOUT A TIP OR TWO
FOR THE OUT-OF-TOWNERS

00:12.125 --> 00:14.166
ABOUT OUR
DRIVING REGULATIONS, HUH?

00:14.166 --> 00:16.000
HERE IN LOS ANGELES,

00:16.000 --> 00:19.000
A YELLOW LIGHT MEANS
UPDATE YOUR FACEBOOK STATUS.

00:19.000 --> 00:20.250
AH!

00:20.250 --> 00:23.416
I JUST UPDATED MY FACEBOOK
STATUS -- BORED!

00:23.416 --> 00:25.833
[ LAUGHTER ]
HEY, THIS IS WHERE
<i>I </i>MAKE THE JOKES.

00:25.833 --> 00:26.875
WE'RE READY
WHEN YOU ARE.

00:26.875 --> 00:27.833
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:27.833 --> 00:29.291
YEAH.

00:29.291 --> 00:31.250
HOW DO I DEAL
WITH HECKLERS?

00:31.250 --> 00:34.833
I'M A PROFESSIONAL COMEDIAN.
IT'S JUST PART OF THE JOB.

00:34.833 --> 00:38.416
THE PART THAT KEEPS YOU FROM
COMPLETELY LIKING YOURSELF.

00:38.416 --> 00:40.583
BROADCAST STANDARDS OVER HERE
WON'T LET US DO THE BIT

00:40.583 --> 00:42.833
WHERE PIGGY JUMPS
INTO A VAT OF CHOCOLATE PUDDING.

00:42.833 --> 00:44.750
THE NETWORK
HAS CONCERNS

00:44.750 --> 00:47.458
THAT A CHILD MIGHT JUMP
INTO A VAT OF PUDDING AT HOME

00:47.458 --> 00:49.083
AND DROWN.
[ SIGHS ]

00:49.083 --> 00:50.458
WHO HAS A VAT OF PUDDING
AT HOME?

00:50.458 --> 00:53.166
YOU KNOW AMERICA STRUGGLES
WITH PORTION SIZE.

00:53.166 --> 00:54.625
SORRY, GONZO.
YOU KNOW.

00:54.625 --> 00:56.458
OH, UM,
HEY, KERMIT?
YEAH?

00:56.458 --> 00:59.625
UH, THERE'S A LECTURE ON
ASTRAL PROJECTION NEXT FRIDAY.

00:59.625 --> 01:00.958
OH, OH, SO YOU WANT
THE DAY OFF?

01:00.958 --> 01:02.458
NO, I'LL BE HERE.

01:02.458 --> 01:04.458
I JUST WANTED YOU TO KNOW
THAT I'LL BE THERE, TOO.

01:04.458 --> 01:06.250
HEY, SAM.

01:06.250 --> 01:07.625
HMM.

01:07.625 --> 01:10.250
SO, UH, ANYTHING ELSE?

01:10.250 --> 01:11.500
HELLO?

01:11.500 --> 01:13.375
DID YOU HEAR THAT?

01:13.375 --> 01:15.708
JANICE JUST SAID,
"HEY, SAM."

01:15.708 --> 01:17.375
[ LAUGHS ]

01:17.375 --> 01:19.083
NOW, THAT COULD MEAN
ONE OF TWO THINGS --

01:19.083 --> 01:22.583
"HELLO TO YOU,
MY COLLEAGUE SAM."

01:22.583 --> 01:30.583
OR THE MORE OBVIOUS, "I'VE LOVED
YOU FOR A MILLION LIFETIMES."

01:30.583 --> 01:32.166
[ SIGHS ]

01:32.166 --> 01:34.958
AHH...

01:34.958 --> 01:36.166
WHOA!

01:36.166 --> 01:38.125
[ LAUGHS ]

01:38.125 --> 01:39.833
YOU KNOW, THE BEST THING
ABOUT THIS GUN

01:39.833 --> 01:42.458
IS IT'S HANDY IF YOU'RE EVER
BEING ROBBED BY A TOPLESS GUY.

01:42.458 --> 01:43.708
[ LAUGHTER ]
OH.
OH, THAT WAS BAD.

01:43.708 --> 01:44.625
YEAH, PRETTY BAD.

01:44.625 --> 01:45.958
ALL RIGHT, GUYS,

01:45.958 --> 01:48.875
ONE LAST ONE
BEFORE WE START THE SHOW!

01:48.875 --> 01:50.500
[ AUDIENCE SHOUTING ]

01:50.500 --> 01:53.583
[ GROANS ] HUH, JAMMED.

01:53.583 --> 01:56.500
OH, OH, I LIKE
WHERE THIS IS GOING.

01:56.500 --> 01:57.208
OH, YEAH.

01:57.208 --> 01:57.958
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

01:57.958 --> 01:59.291
AW.

01:59.291 --> 02:01.458
SORRY, FOLKS.
IT'S JUST NOT WO--

02:01.458 --> 02:03.291
[ GRUNTS ] OH!

02:03.291 --> 02:06.083
OH. HA!
I GOT THE T-SHIRT!

02:06.083 --> 02:06.875
[ LAUGHS ]

02:06.875 --> 02:08.583
HEY, STAT--
STATLER?

02:08.583 --> 02:10.000
[ GROANS ]

02:10.000 --> 02:12.291
HMM. AT LEAST
I GOT THE T-SHIRT.

02:12.291 --> 02:13.875
[ GROANS ]

02:13.875 --> 02:16.583
♪♪

02:16.583 --> 02:18.083
[ DING ]

02:19.583 --> 02:20.875
♪ OOH! ♪

02:23.291 --> 02:24.958
YEAH!

02:24.958 --> 02:26.708
♪ UNH! ♪

02:26.708 --> 02:28.958
HMM. TIME TO
GET THINGS STARTED.

02:31.875 --> 02:34.125
HA HA HA!

02:34.125 --> 02:37.000
HEY, STATLER, MAKE SURE
THEY TAKE YOU TO COUNTY MEDICAL.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.958
THEY'RE PRETTY LOOSEY-GOOSEY
WITH THE MEDS OVER THERE.

02:38.958 --> 02:40.375
[ GROANS ]
[ LAUGHS ]

02:40.375 --> 02:42.708
KERMIT.
OH, BOY.

02:42.708 --> 02:45.750
IF YOU NEED HELP
COVERING THIS UP,

02:45.750 --> 02:47.875
I'M GREAT
AT HIDING THINGS.

02:47.875 --> 02:50.375
HEY, FOZZIE, ARE YOU GONNA BE
OKAY TO GET BACK OUT THERE?

02:50.375 --> 02:52.333
HMM? ME?

02:52.333 --> 02:53.833
SURE.

02:53.833 --> 02:55.208
I'M A PRO.
OKAY.

02:55.208 --> 02:57.083
I KNOW THE PERFECT WAY
TO WIN BACK THE CROWD.

02:57.083 --> 02:59.500
I'LL BUST OUT
THE OLD CANDY SLINGSHOT

02:59.500 --> 03:01.083
AND SOME JAWBREAKERS, YEAH!
NO, NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO.

03:01.083 --> 03:03.750
FOZZIE, JUST GET OUT THERE
AND TELL YOUR JOKES.

03:03.750 --> 03:05.000
YEAH.
ALL RIGHT.

03:05.000 --> 03:06.416
[ SIGHS ]

03:06.416 --> 03:08.416
WHAT ABOUT GUMBALLS?
JOKES!

03:08.416 --> 03:09.958
[ SIGHS ]

03:09.958 --> 03:11.000
[ HUMMING ]

03:11.000 --> 03:13.083
OH.
DID YOU HEAR?

03:13.083 --> 03:14.583
SOME POOR MAN
IN THE CROWD

03:14.583 --> 03:17.000
GOT SHOT IN THE FACE
WITH A T-SHIRT.

03:17.000 --> 03:18.000
NO!

03:18.000 --> 03:19.000
WHAT'S GOOD TO EAT?

03:19.000 --> 03:20.875
OOH.
EN FORGI SOYGAN.

03:20.875 --> 03:22.875
SWEDISH SUSHI?
WHAT THE HECK IS THAT?

03:22.875 --> 03:24.000
OOH.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.458
FER DER MEATBALL
FER DER SOYGAN SAUCE.

03:26.458 --> 03:28.708
UH...YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M GONNA PASS.

03:28.708 --> 03:30.583
OKAY.
UGH.

03:30.583 --> 03:32.375
[ MEEPING ]

03:32.375 --> 03:34.375
OH, I SHALL INQUIRE.

03:34.375 --> 03:36.583
EXCUSE ME, MR. BOBO.
YES, SIR.

03:36.583 --> 03:39.583
WILL THE CREW STILL BE GATHERING
FOR DRINKS AFTER THE SHOW?

03:39.583 --> 03:41.583
I CALLED ROWLF
AND HE'S HOLDING OUR TABLE.

03:41.583 --> 03:42.208
EXCELLENT!

03:42.208 --> 03:43.333
BECAUSE THIS EVENING,

03:43.333 --> 03:45.375
MY PhD STANDS FOR
"PRETTY HARD DRINKING."

03:45.375 --> 03:46.375
OH.

03:46.375 --> 03:47.500
NOT REALLY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:47.500 --> 03:49.500
IT REFERS TO
MY ADVANCED ACADEMIC DEGREE.

03:49.500 --> 03:50.875
OH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:52.333 --> 03:53.958
CHEF.

03:53.958 --> 03:55.708
DOES EVERYONE GO OUT
AFTER THE SHOW?

03:56.875 --> 04:01.708
ERHHHH...

04:01.708 --> 04:02.875
[ APPLAUSE IN DISTANCE ]

04:02.875 --> 04:04.458
[ GROANS ]

04:04.458 --> 04:06.000
KERMIT!

04:06.000 --> 04:06.875
Miss Piggy: KERMIT!
GOT IT.

04:06.875 --> 04:08.000
-IT'S MISS PIGGY!
-THERE SHE IS!

04:08.000 --> 04:08.625
[ WHISTLE, APPLAUSE ]

04:08.625 --> 04:10.125
KER--
HELLO, EVERYONE.

04:10.125 --> 04:12.083
KERMIT,
I NEED TO TALK WITH YOU.

04:12.083 --> 04:13.458
WELL,
D-DON'T WORRY, PIGGY.

04:13.458 --> 04:15.208
I DON'T THINK HE'S GONNA SUE
AS LONG AS WE FIND HIS TEETH.

04:15.208 --> 04:17.416
GOT 'EM!

04:17.416 --> 04:20.000
LOOK AT ME.
I'M BRADLEY COOPERS.

04:20.000 --> 04:21.416
[ LAUGHS ]

04:21.416 --> 04:22.708
I GUESS WE FOUND THEM.

04:22.708 --> 04:24.458
DID YOU KNOW THE CREW
GOES OUT AFTER THE SHOW

04:24.458 --> 04:26.333
AND THEY'VE NEVER
INVITED ME?
OH. [ CLEARS THROAT ]

04:26.333 --> 04:28.708
UH, YEAH, YEAH.
LET'S TALK.
WHAT? WHAT?

04:28.708 --> 04:30.875
LISTEN, PIGGY, THEY DON'T INVITE
ME, EITHER, YOU KNOW?

04:30.875 --> 04:32.250
THEY DON'T WANT
THE BOSSES THERE.

04:32.250 --> 04:34.000
IT'S THEIR TIME TO BLOW OFF
SOME STEAM ABOUT WORK.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.708
OH, HEY, EVERYBODY!
EVERYBODY!

04:36.708 --> 04:38.375
BEAKER DOES
THE BEST PIGGY.

04:38.375 --> 04:39.625
WATCH THIS.

04:39.625 --> 04:42.166
"OH, MISS PIGGY,
CAN I GET YOU ANYTHING?"

04:42.166 --> 04:44.375
ME, ME, ME, ME, MOI.

04:44.375 --> 04:47.583
ME, ME, ME, ME, ME,
ME, ME, ME, ME, ME!

04:47.583 --> 04:49.166
[ LAUGHTER ]

04:49.166 --> 04:50.750
OH! IT'S LIKE
SHE'S IN THE ROOM.

04:50.750 --> 04:52.291
TRUST ME,
YOU DON'T WANT TO GO.

04:52.291 --> 04:54.291
OF COURSE
I DON'T WANT TO GO.

04:54.291 --> 04:56.750
THEY OWN THINGS LIKE MINI VANS
AND LAUNDRY BASKETS.

04:56.750 --> 04:58.333
I JUST WANT TO BE ASKED.
MAKE IT HAPPEN.

04:58.333 --> 04:59.458
WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.

04:59.458 --> 05:01.250
YOU WANT ME TO FORCE THE CREW
TO ASK YOU OUT

05:01.250 --> 05:02.458
JUST SO
YOU CAN SAY NO?
YEAH.

05:02.458 --> 05:03.875
PIGGY, BE RATIONAL.

05:03.875 --> 05:05.166
[ Chuckling ]
OH, KERMIT,

05:05.166 --> 05:08.375
THAT DOESN'T SOUND LIKE ME
AT ALL.

05:08.375 --> 05:10.250
AH, WHERE ARE YOU FROM,
SIR?

05:10.250 --> 05:12.583
PHOENIX.
PHOENIX, HUH?

05:12.583 --> 05:15.750
YOU KNOW, IT'S SO HOT
IN PHOENIX THAT...

05:19.583 --> 05:21.875
OH, WHO CARES?

05:21.875 --> 05:24.166
WE'RE ALL JUST
HANGING BY A THREAD.

05:24.166 --> 05:26.875
TOMORROW'S PROMISED
TO NO ONE.

05:26.875 --> 05:28.458
ENJOY THE SHOW.

05:28.458 --> 05:30.583
[ MICROPHONE THUDS, FEEDBACK ]

05:30.583 --> 05:32.875
BRAVO!
[ LAUGHS ]

05:35.375 --> 05:36.583
OH, COME ON, KERMIT.

05:36.583 --> 05:37.958
DON'T MAKE US ASK MISS PIGGY
TO GO OUT WITH US.

05:37.958 --> 05:39.125
YEAH, LIKE EVERY TIME
I SOCIALIZE

05:39.125 --> 05:40.333
WITH ONE OF
MY LADY BOSSES,

05:40.333 --> 05:42.208
THEY WIND UP
FALLING IN LOVE WITH ME,

05:42.208 --> 05:44.958
IT GETS AWKWARD,
AND ONE OF US HAS TO GO.

05:44.958 --> 05:47.000
SINCE I DON'T REALLY DO
ANYTHING, IT'S USUALLY ME.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.125
YEAH, GUYS, BUT COME ON.
SHE'S NOT GONNA SAY YES.

05:49.125 --> 05:50.583
YOU KNOW, SHE JUST WANTS
TO FEEL RESPECTED,

05:50.583 --> 05:52.750
SO MAKE IT SOUND SINCERE,
PLEASE?

05:52.750 --> 05:54.500
OKAY, OKAY.
I'LL DO IT. I'LL DO IT.
OH, GOOD.

05:54.500 --> 05:56.000
YOU KNOW I PLAYED HAMLET
IN HIGH SCHOOL?

05:56.000 --> 05:57.291
OH.

05:57.291 --> 05:59.083
IT WAS A VERY CONTROVERSIAL
CASTING CHOICE

05:59.083 --> 06:01.708
BECAUSE I WAS NOT
VERY GOOD.
WELL, IT --

06:01.708 --> 06:03.333
Piggy:
GOOD NIGHT, EVERYBODY.
OH, H-HERE SHE COMES.
HERE SHE COMES.

06:03.333 --> 06:05.000
OH, OH.
GET HOME SAFE.

06:05.000 --> 06:06.000
UH, YEAH, YEAH.
GOOD NIGHT.
THANK YOU.

06:06.000 --> 06:07.333
OH.

06:07.333 --> 06:09.166
OH. COOL.
MAYBE
TOMORROW NIGHT.

06:09.166 --> 06:10.708
I'M SORRY. DID SOMEBODY
INVITE ME TO SOMETHING?

06:10.708 --> 06:12.000
OH, UH [CLEARS THROAT]
PEPE. PEPE.

06:12.000 --> 06:13.583
[ STAMMERS ]

06:13.583 --> 06:14.625
RIGHT HERE. YEAH.

06:14.625 --> 06:16.416
M-M-M-M-MISS PIGGY?
YES?

06:16.416 --> 06:19.583
Sí.
UH, WOULD YOU...

06:19.583 --> 06:21.291
SHOOT. LINE?
OH, UH...

06:21.291 --> 06:24.625
OH. ARE YOU INVITING MOI TO GO
TO ROWLF'S TONIGHT WITH VOUS?

06:24.625 --> 06:25.458
Sí, Sí.
THIS WAS MY LINE.

06:25.458 --> 06:27.166
OH!

06:27.166 --> 06:29.333
WELL, THAT IS SUCH
A SWEET INVITATION.
WELL --

06:29.333 --> 06:31.958
BUT UNFORTUNATELY,
I'VE GOT A MASSAGE APPOINTMENT,

06:31.958 --> 06:33.458
SO I WON'T BE ABLE
TO JOIN YOU.
AWW.

06:33.458 --> 06:35.208
BUT THANK YOU.
WELL, THAT'S SO SAD.

06:35.208 --> 06:37.291
THANK YOU.
THAT IS SO DEAR OF YOU.
OH, NO.

06:37.291 --> 06:39.000
THANK YOU.
WE LOVE YOU.
YES!

06:39.000 --> 06:40.125
WELL, GOOD NIGHT.
SEE YOU NEXT TIME.

06:40.125 --> 06:41.291
OH, THANK YOU
SO MUCH, GUYS.
[ LAUGHS ]

06:41.291 --> 06:42.583
LISTEN, YOU HAVE REALLY
MADE MY LIFE EASIER.

06:42.583 --> 06:44.708
CHANGED MY MIND!
SEE YOU THERE.

06:44.708 --> 06:47.125
[ GIGGLES ]
FUN WITH PIGGY!

06:47.125 --> 06:48.166
FUN, FUN, FUN.

06:48.166 --> 06:49.500
OH.

06:49.500 --> 06:51.333
UH...

06:51.333 --> 06:53.500
WELL, I MEAN, UH,
YOU HEARD HER.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.708
IT'S --
IT'S GONNA BE FUN, RIGHT?
WH--

06:55.708 --> 06:57.250
FUN, FUN, FUN.
WHAT'D YOU DO?

06:57.250 --> 06:59.416
EXCUSE ME.
KERMIT, WHAT'D YOU DO?

06:59.416 --> 07:01.583
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

07:01.583 --> 07:03.625
OH, HELLO, KERMIT.

07:03.625 --> 07:05.750
WASN'T THAT SWEET OF THE CREW
TO INVITE ME LIKE THAT?

07:05.750 --> 07:07.625
IT WAS SO UNEXPECTED.

07:07.625 --> 07:09.833
ARE YOU INSANE?
YOU SAID YOU'D SAY NO.

07:09.833 --> 07:12.375
I KNOW,
BUT THEN SOMETHING HAPPENED.

07:12.375 --> 07:14.000
WHAT?
I SAID YES.

07:14.000 --> 07:15.458
DO THESE DIAMONDS
MAKE ME LOOK RELATABLE?

07:15.458 --> 07:18.000
WHY DID YOU SAY YES?!
YOU PROMISED ME YOU WOULDN'T!

07:18.000 --> 07:21.000
KERMIT, BACK WHEN I WAS
A YOUNG CHORUS GIRL...
[ SIGHS ]

07:21.000 --> 07:24.375
...EVERY NOW AND THEN, A STAR
WOULD JOIN US AFTER THE SHOW

07:24.375 --> 07:25.750
AND IT WOULD BE
SUCH A THRILL.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
[ MUTTERING ]

07:25.750 --> 07:27.708
NOW IT'S TIME FOR ME

07:27.708 --> 07:30.375
TO BRIGHTEN UP
MY CREW'S DRAB LITTLE LIVES.

07:30.375 --> 07:32.416
DRAB LIVES.
THEY WANT MOI.

07:32.416 --> 07:34.083
THEY DESERVE MOI.
[ SIGHS ]

07:34.083 --> 07:36.625
AND THEY'RE ABOUT TO GET
A BIG STEAMING PILE OF MOI!

07:36.625 --> 07:38.250
OH. YOU...

07:38.250 --> 07:40.458
OF COURSE PIGGY SAID YES.

07:40.458 --> 07:42.333
SHE'S SO DESPERATE TO BE LOVED
BY EVERYBODY

07:42.333 --> 07:44.958
THAT SHE CONNED ME INTO BEING
A PART OF HER SORDID SCHEME.

07:44.958 --> 07:46.208
[ SIGHS ]

07:46.208 --> 07:47.708
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:47.708 --> 07:51.125
GOT TO GIVE IT TO HER.
SHE'S REALLY GOOD AT THAT.

07:51.125 --> 07:52.125
[ SIGHS ]

07:52.125 --> 07:53.375
ANY KNOWN ALLERGIES?

07:53.375 --> 07:55.583
HMM?
OH, JUST CHOCOLATE.

07:55.583 --> 07:56.833
YEAH.

07:56.833 --> 07:58.458
I GOT INTO
MY CUPBOARD ONCE.

07:58.458 --> 08:00.208
ATE A LOT OF IT.

08:00.208 --> 08:02.875
GOT REAL SICK, AND THERE
WAS TALK OF PUTTING ME DOWN.

08:02.875 --> 08:05.291
UH -- OH, WAIT.

08:05.291 --> 08:07.416
NO, THAT --
THAT WAS MY DOG.

08:07.416 --> 08:10.583
[ GROANS ]

08:12.083 --> 08:14.458
HELLO.
HUH?! HUH?! AAH!

08:14.458 --> 08:17.083
YOU! WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
YOU COME TO FINISH ME OFF?

08:17.083 --> 08:18.750
I WAS WORRIED
ABOUT YOU.

08:18.750 --> 08:21.875
OH, YEAH? WELL, THAT'S
THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN US.

08:21.875 --> 08:23.458
IF I EVER SHOT YOU,

08:23.458 --> 08:25.708
YOU'D BE LYING FACEDOWN
IN FRONT OF MY FIREPLACE.

08:25.708 --> 08:27.333
[ LAUGHS ]

08:27.333 --> 08:29.166
OH, OH, OH!

08:29.166 --> 08:30.208
IT HURTS TO LAUGH.

08:30.208 --> 08:32.708
[ SIGHS ]

08:32.708 --> 08:34.458
SO, I GUESS I'M SAFE
WITH<i>YOU </i>IN THE ROOM.

08:34.458 --> 08:35.875
[ LAUGHS ] OH.

08:35.875 --> 08:37.500
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I DON'T HAVE TO TAKE THIS.

08:37.500 --> 08:40.458
I JUST CAME HERE
TO SAY I'M SORRY

08:40.458 --> 08:43.000
AND TO --
AND TO GIVE YOU THESE.

08:43.000 --> 08:44.458
SO, I'M GONNA GO.

08:44.458 --> 08:46.000
[ GROANS ]

08:46.000 --> 08:50.375
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO CAME TO VISIT ME.

08:50.375 --> 08:51.875
WALDORF NEVER SHOWED UP?

08:51.875 --> 08:54.708
NAH.
HE'S AFRAID OF HOSPITALS.

08:54.708 --> 08:56.708
HE FELL ASLEEP
IN THE WAITING ROOM ONCE

08:56.708 --> 08:58.416
AND THEY TOOK HIM
TO THE MORGUE.

08:58.416 --> 09:00.875
YOU KNOW, YOU MIGHT HAVE
MORE VISITORS

09:00.875 --> 09:02.875
IF YOU WERE JUST
A LITTLE LESS...

09:02.875 --> 09:04.708
[ GROANS ]
...SOUL-CRUSHING.

09:04.708 --> 09:07.000
YEAH.

09:07.000 --> 09:08.750
I GOT LOTS OF PROBLEMS.

09:08.750 --> 09:13.708
LOOK, I-I DO
HAVE TO GO, BUT...

09:13.708 --> 09:15.125
LET ME KNOW
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING, ALL RIGHT?

09:15.125 --> 09:16.458
YEAH.

09:18.083 --> 09:19.500
HEY, WAIT.

09:19.500 --> 09:20.750
MY READING GLASSES BROKE

09:20.750 --> 09:23.083
WHEN YOU KNOCKED ME
ARSE OVER TEA KETTLE.

09:23.083 --> 09:25.166
MAYBE YOU COULD STOP BY
THE DRUG STORE

09:25.166 --> 09:26.583
AND GET ME A NEW PAIR.

09:26.583 --> 09:28.291
NO PROBLEM.
OKAY.

09:28.291 --> 09:29.875
AND MY NECK'S HURTING.

09:29.875 --> 09:32.083
UH, WOULD YOU MIND GOING
TO THE BED STORE

09:32.083 --> 09:35.250
AND PICKING ME UP ONE OF
THOSE MEMORY FOAM PILLOWS?

09:35.250 --> 09:38.000
I NEED THE ONE
THAT REMEMBERS MY HEAD.

09:38.000 --> 09:40.125
HATE STARTING OVER
EVERY TIME I LAY DOWN.

09:40.125 --> 09:42.458
UM...ANYTHING ELSE?

09:42.458 --> 09:44.291
YEAH, AN OSCILLATING FAN.

09:44.291 --> 09:46.750
I LOVE IT
WHEN I'M JUST LAYING THERE

09:46.750 --> 09:52.208
AND THEN
ALL OF A SUDDEN...WIND.

09:52.208 --> 09:54.875
LET ME GRAB A PEN.

09:54.875 --> 09:57.208
Piggy: WHAT A DAY,
RIGHT, GUYS?

09:57.208 --> 09:59.625
I MEAN, TOTAL DRAG.
[ LAUGHS ]

09:59.625 --> 10:01.750
OH, YEAH.
WHY, JUST THIS MORNING,
I'M LYING BY THE POOL

10:01.750 --> 10:05.458
AND MY LANDSCAPE DESIGNER
STARTS BRAGGING ABOUT HIS KIDS.

10:05.458 --> 10:07.083
DON'T YOU HATE IT
WHEN THAT HAPPENS?

10:07.083 --> 10:08.958
UH, WE DON'T
HAVE THOSE.

10:08.958 --> 10:11.166
WHAT, LANDSCAPE DESIGNERS?
LANDSCAPES.

10:11.166 --> 10:13.500
WELL, YOU DON'T HAVE TO IMAGINE
HOW ANNOYING IT IS

10:13.500 --> 10:16.458
TO BE HELD CAPTIVE
BY SOME BLOWHARD

10:16.458 --> 10:18.333
YAPPING ABOUT
THEIR PERSONAL LIFE.

10:18.333 --> 10:19.458
WE CERTAINLY DON'T.

10:19.458 --> 10:21.750
ANYWAY,
THEN I GOT TO WORK<i>FINALLY.</i>

10:21.750 --> 10:23.625
THE LIMO WAS STUCK
IN TRAFFIC...

10:23.625 --> 10:25.000
FOR THE LOVE OF MIKE.

10:25.000 --> 10:26.958
AYE, SOMEBODY PEEL AND EAT ME
ALREADY.

10:26.958 --> 10:28.458
I'VE HAD MORE FUN
IN A GLUE TRAP.
MM-HMM.

10:28.458 --> 10:32.291
ANYWAY, AND THAT IS WHY I ALWAYS
TAKE A HELICOPTER TO CATALINA.

10:32.291 --> 10:33.291
KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

10:33.291 --> 10:34.125
Ed: PIGGY!

10:34.125 --> 10:37.083
OH, MY GOD. ED HELMS!

10:37.083 --> 10:38.000
ED HELMS!

10:38.000 --> 10:40.208
HEY, YOU SEXY SIDE
OF SAUSAGE.

10:40.208 --> 10:41.750
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
SINCE MY BIRTHDAY PARTY.

10:41.750 --> 10:44.458
AT CHUCK E. CHEESE.
YEAH.

10:44.458 --> 10:46.333
FASCINATING CHOICE OF VENUE
FOR AN ADULT.

10:46.333 --> 10:47.625
YEAH, WELL,

10:47.625 --> 10:49.083
MY NIECE HAD A PARTY THERE
AND DIDN'T INVITE ME,

10:49.083 --> 10:50.833
SO I HAD MY OWN PARTY
AND DIDN'T INVITE HER.

10:50.833 --> 10:52.125
[ RIZZO LAUGHS ]
PAYBACK!

10:52.125 --> 10:53.000
[ LAUGHS ]

10:53.000 --> 10:54.500
YOUR TURN
TO CRY NOW, MADISON.

10:54.500 --> 10:55.583
EVEN IF YOU ARE 11.

10:55.583 --> 10:56.958
[ LAUGHS ]

10:56.958 --> 10:58.708
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
SIT DOWN. JOIN US.

10:58.708 --> 11:00.083
I'M JUST HANGING
WITH MY CREW.
YEAH, PLEASE.

11:00.083 --> 11:01.000
NO, NO, NO.
I DON'T WANT TO INTERRUPT.

11:01.000 --> 11:03.000
NO, NO, NO, NO, SIT.
JOIN US. JOIN US.

11:03.000 --> 11:05.166
ANIMAL GO GET DRINKS.

11:05.166 --> 11:06.750
YEAH, YEAH, PLEASE.
RIGHT HERE, BUDDY.

11:06.750 --> 11:08.750
HEY, ALL RIGHT.

11:08.750 --> 11:11.458
HEY, UH, UH,
WHERE DO I KNOW YOU FROM?

11:11.458 --> 11:12.875
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE "THE OFFICE."

11:12.875 --> 11:15.083
OH, OH.
WE WORK TOGETHER.

11:15.083 --> 11:16.750
OH, MAN,
I'M SORRY, BROTHER.

11:16.750 --> 11:18.416
I'M FLOYD.
I'M WITH THE BAND.

11:18.416 --> 11:19.708
HEY, IT'S GOOD
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

11:19.708 --> 11:21.958
HAVE A DRINK.
OKAY.

11:21.958 --> 11:25.000
UH, I'M JANICE,
AND, UM, YOU KNOW,

11:25.000 --> 11:26.416
I'M, LIKE,
ALSO WITH THE BAND.

11:26.416 --> 11:27.875
IS THAT RIGHT?
FOR SURE.

11:27.875 --> 11:29.583
YEAH, COOL.
MM-HMM.

11:29.583 --> 11:31.166
I LOVE BANDS.
REALLY?

11:31.166 --> 11:33.083
YEAH, WHAT, UH --
WHAT INSTRUMENT DO YOU PLAY?

11:33.083 --> 11:34.958
OH, WOW, LIKE,
I PLAY THE GUITAR.

11:34.958 --> 11:36.208
WOW.

11:36.208 --> 11:38.875
DO YOU PLAY AN INSTRUMENT?
I-I-I PLAY SOME BANJO.

11:38.875 --> 11:41.000
OH, I LOVE THE BANJO.

11:41.000 --> 11:42.208
[ SIGHS ]

11:42.208 --> 11:44.458
I HAD TO RUN AROUND TOWN
ALL NIGHT,

11:44.458 --> 11:48.333
BUT I FINALLY GOT EVERYTHING
ON STATLER'S LIST.

11:48.333 --> 11:51.000
YOU KNOW, IT REALLY FEELS GOOD
TO DO SOMETHING NICE

11:51.000 --> 11:52.708
FOR SOMEBODY
YOU SHOT IN THE FACE.

11:52.708 --> 11:56.291
STATLER!

11:56.291 --> 11:58.958
STATLER, WAKE UP.

11:58.958 --> 12:02.458
I GOT YOU
EVERYTHING YOU ASKED FOR.

12:03.250 --> 12:04.291
STATLER?

12:08.208 --> 12:11.250
NOOOOOO!

12:11.250 --> 12:14.500
EVERY FOREST RANGER
WILL TELL YOU THE SAME THING.

12:14.500 --> 12:18.208
MOST BEAR ATTACKS DO NOT HAPPEN
BECAUSE OF HUNGER.

12:18.208 --> 12:22.875
THEY HAPPEN BECAUSE SOME BEAR...
GOT HIS FEELINGS HURT.

12:22.875 --> 12:24.000
[ SIGHS ]

12:24.000 --> 12:25.875
♪ IF YOU WANNA BE MY LOVER ♪

12:25.875 --> 12:28.500
♪ YOU GOTTA GET
WITH MY FRIENDS ♪

12:28.500 --> 12:30.125
♪ MAKE IT LAST FOREVER ♪

12:30.125 --> 12:32.583
♪ FRIENDSHIP NEVER ENDS ♪♪

12:32.583 --> 12:33.958
♪ LOVE SHACK ♪

12:33.958 --> 12:36.500
♪ BABY, LOVE SHACK ♪

12:36.500 --> 12:37.583
♪ LOVE SHACK ♪

12:37.583 --> 12:39.291
♪ BABY, LOVE SHACK ♪

12:39.291 --> 12:40.000
EVERYBODY!

12:40.000 --> 12:41.250
♪ LOVE SHACK ♪

12:41.250 --> 12:42.458
♪ BABY, LOVE SHACK ♪

12:42.458 --> 12:43.458
Woman: WHOO!

12:43.458 --> 12:44.500
♪ LOVE SHACK ♪

12:44.500 --> 12:46.375
♪ BABY, LOVE SHACK ♪

12:46.375 --> 12:50.333
[ "RAPPER'S DELIGHT" PLAYS ]

12:50.333 --> 12:51.708
♪ I SAID A HIP HOP ♪

12:51.708 --> 12:53.833
♪ THE HIPPIE, THE HIPPIE,
TO THE HIP-HIP HOP ♪

12:53.833 --> 12:55.333
♪ AND YOU DON'T STOP,
THE ROCK IT ♪

12:55.333 --> 12:57.250
♪ TO THE BANG-BANG BOOGIE,
SAY UP JUMP THE BOOGIE ♪

12:57.250 --> 12:59.166
♪ TO THE RHYTHM OF THE BOOGIE,
THE BEAT ♪

12:59.166 --> 13:01.458
♪ NOW, WHAT YOU HEAR
IS NOT A TEST ♪

13:01.458 --> 13:03.208
♪ I'M RAPPIN' TO THE BEAT ♪♪

13:03.208 --> 13:06.250
♪ LOVER'S IN LOVE
AND THE OTHER'S RUN AWAY ♪

13:06.250 --> 13:09.416
♪ LOVER IS CRYING
'CAUSE THE OTHER WON'T STAY ♪

13:09.416 --> 13:12.000
♪ SOME OF US HOVER WHEN
WE'RE WEEPING FOR THE OTHER ♪

13:12.000 --> 13:14.458
♪ WHO WAS DYING SINCE THE DAY
THEY WERE BORN, WELL... ♪♪

13:14.458 --> 13:17.458
♪ I GOT FLOWERS ♪

13:17.458 --> 13:18.750
♪ IN THE SPRING ♪

13:18.750 --> 13:19.500
AHH.

13:19.500 --> 13:20.708
Beaker: ♪ ME ME ME ♪

13:20.708 --> 13:22.375
♪ I GOT YOU ♪

13:22.375 --> 13:23.708
♪ ME ME ME ♪

13:23.708 --> 13:26.375
♪ TO WEAR MY RING ♪

13:26.375 --> 13:27.000
TAKE IT, BEAKER!

13:27.000 --> 13:28.291
♪ ME ME ME ME ♪

13:28.291 --> 13:30.375
Woman: WHOO-HOO!

13:30.375 --> 13:32.166
♪ ME ME ME ME ♪

13:32.166 --> 13:33.166
MY HERO.

13:33.166 --> 13:36.416
♪ ME ME-ME ME ME ♪

13:36.416 --> 13:40.166
♪ ME ME ME ME-E-E-E-E ♪♪

13:40.166 --> 13:42.166
♪ AND ME, THE GROOVE,
AND MY FRIENDS ♪

13:42.166 --> 13:44.083
♪ ARE GONNA TRY TO MOVE
YOUR FEET ♪

13:44.083 --> 13:46.458
All: WHOO!
♪ SEE, I AM WONDER MIKE ♪

13:46.458 --> 13:48.583
♪ AND I'D LIKE TO SAY HELLO ♪
All: HELLO!

13:48.583 --> 13:50.625
♪ TO THE BLACK, TO THE WHITE,
THE RED, AND THE BROWN ♪

13:50.625 --> 13:52.583
♪ THE PURPLE AND YELLOW ♪

13:52.583 --> 13:55.333
♪ BUT FIRST I GOTTA BANG-BANG
THE BOOGIE TO THE BOOGIE ♪

13:55.333 --> 13:57.833
♪ SAY UP JUMP THE BOOGIE TO THE
BANG-BANG BOOGIE, LET'S ROCK ♪♪

13:57.833 --> 14:05.708
♪ DID YOU EVER KNOW
THAT YOU'RE MY HERO? ♪

14:05.708 --> 14:11.250
♪ AND EVERYTHING
I WOULD LIKE TO BE ♪

14:11.250 --> 14:13.166
THANK YOU.

14:13.166 --> 14:18.083
♪ I CAN FLY
HIGHER THAN AN EAGLE ♪

14:18.083 --> 14:20.583
[ LAUGHS ]

14:20.583 --> 14:25.166
♪ FOR YOU ARE THE WIND
BENEATH MY WINGS ♪♪

14:25.166 --> 14:26.083
[ MICROPHONE THUDS, FEEDBACK ]

14:26.083 --> 14:29.291
♪ UP AND DOWN THE BOULEVARD ♪

14:29.291 --> 14:32.458
♪ THEIR SHADOWS SEARCHING
IN THE NIGHT ♪
HEY, UH -- HEY, PIGGY.

14:32.458 --> 14:34.250
HMM?
PIGGY,
THANKS FOR THIS,

14:34.250 --> 14:36.583
BUT, UH, WE GOT
A BIG DAY AT WORK TOMORROW.

14:36.583 --> 14:38.583
♪ STREETLIGHTS, PEOPLE ♪
SO DO WHAT I DO.
GO IN LATE.

14:38.583 --> 14:40.333
WH--
UH, I DON'T KNOW.

14:40.333 --> 14:43.125
KERMIT GETS KIND OF CRANKY
IF WE DON'T GET IN BY 9:00.

14:43.125 --> 14:44.125
♪ ...FIND EMOTION ♪
I WAS LATE ONCE,

14:44.125 --> 14:47.708
AND HE SAID "GOOD GRIEF"
LIKE 10 TIMES IN A ROW.

14:47.708 --> 14:49.125
♪ HIDING SOMEWHERE
IN THE NIGHT ♪
I NEVER WANT TO LIVE
THROUGH THAT AGAIN.

14:49.125 --> 14:51.333
OH, WHO CARES WHAT THAT
LITTLE GREEN BUZZKILL WANTS?

14:51.333 --> 14:53.125
WE'RE HAVING FUN!

14:53.125 --> 14:54.583
GOOD GRIEF,
YOU'RE RIGHT!

14:54.583 --> 14:56.500
[ GASPS ]
LISTEN TO ME.

14:56.500 --> 14:58.291
I'M SWEARING
LIKE A SAILOR!

14:58.291 --> 14:59.166
[ LAUGHS ]

14:59.166 --> 15:00.166
Ed:
UH, EXCUSE ME.

15:00.166 --> 15:01.333
I DON'T KNOW
WHETHER OR NOT

15:01.333 --> 15:02.875
YOU FOLKS HAVE CONSIDERED
WHETHER OR NOT

15:02.875 --> 15:05.875
YOU SHOULD KEEP BELIEVING,
BUT I SAY...

15:05.875 --> 15:10.958
♪ DON'T STOP BELIEVIN' ♪

15:10.958 --> 15:13.625
♪ HOLD ON TO THAT FEELIN' ♪

15:13.625 --> 15:18.458
♪ STREETLIGHTS, PEOPLE ♪

15:18.458 --> 15:19.875
♪ AHH ♪

15:21.958 --> 15:23.000
HEY, EVERYBODY,

15:23.000 --> 15:25.458
I BROUGHT DOUGHNUTS TO HELP YOU
FORGET ABOUT LAST NIGHT.

15:25.458 --> 15:27.833
UH...EVERYBODY?

15:27.833 --> 15:28.833
[ TELEPHONE RINGS IN DISTANCE ]

15:28.833 --> 15:30.166
HEY, GUYS?

15:30.166 --> 15:32.500
SCOOTER?

15:32.500 --> 15:33.708
BOBO?

15:33.708 --> 15:36.125
HELLO?

15:36.125 --> 15:39.083
FOZZIE?

15:39.083 --> 15:40.833
GUYS?

15:40.833 --> 15:42.083
PEPE?

15:42.083 --> 15:44.416
WH...

15:44.416 --> 15:45.708
WHAT IS HAPPENING?

15:45.708 --> 15:49.708
[ SCOFFS ] CHEESE LOUISE,
KERMIT, HUH?

15:49.708 --> 15:52.375
STOP YELLING.
I'M HEARING DOUBLE.

15:52.375 --> 15:55.333
YOLANDA?
DID YOU SLEEP HERE?

15:55.333 --> 15:57.166
IS IT MORNING?
YEAH.

15:57.166 --> 15:59.333
THEN, YEAH,
I SLEPT HERE.

15:59.333 --> 16:02.000
[ CHUCKLES ] WE HAD SUCH A GOOD
TIME WITH PIGGY LAST NIGHT.

16:02.000 --> 16:04.208
PIGGY? OUR -- OUR PIGGY?
MISS PIGGY?

16:04.208 --> 16:06.708
OH, YEAH.
SHE IS A BLAST.
HUH.

16:06.708 --> 16:09.000
SHE EVEN INTRODUCED US
TO ED HELMS.
WOW.

16:09.000 --> 16:10.583
HE WAS A FRESH EGG.
YEAH?

16:10.583 --> 16:12.833
AT ONE POINT,
HE WAS SITTING ON MY LAP.

16:12.833 --> 16:15.083
[ Chuckling ]
IT WAS FANTASTIC.
WHA...

16:15.083 --> 16:17.000
I COULDN'T BREATHE,
BUT IT WAS FANTASTIC.

16:17.000 --> 16:19.833
THIS IS SUCH A RELIEF,
BUT WHERE IS EVERYBODY?

16:19.833 --> 16:22.458
PIGGY SAID
THAT WE COULD COME IN AT 2:00.

16:22.458 --> 16:24.000
2:00?
YEAH.

16:24.000 --> 16:25.208
NO, THAT -- THAT'S NOT
GONNA GIVE US ENOUGH TIME

16:25.208 --> 16:26.625
TO GET
THE SHOW TOGETHER.

16:26.625 --> 16:28.458
JUST -- JUST GRAB SOME COFFEE
A-AND CALL EVERYBODY...

16:28.458 --> 16:30.583
[ SIGHS ]
...AND TELL THEM TO GET HERE
AS SOON AS THEY CAN.

16:30.583 --> 16:32.583
OI!
OH, I GOT A POUNDER.

16:32.583 --> 16:34.750
HEY, KERMIT,
BE A HERO.
HMM?

16:34.750 --> 16:37.208
GET ME AN 1/8
OF AN ADVIL, WILL YOU?

16:37.208 --> 16:38.458
[ SIGHS ]

16:38.458 --> 16:39.875
Zoot: OH, MAN.

16:39.875 --> 16:42.250
[ ALL GROANING ]

16:42.250 --> 16:45.416
I WAS HAPPY TO SEE YOU MADE IT
HOME SAFE LAST NIGHT.

16:45.416 --> 16:47.000
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

16:47.000 --> 16:50.083
UH, WELL,
YOU'RE HERE NOW.

16:50.083 --> 16:52.875
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
FOLLOW SOMEBODY HOME TO...

16:52.875 --> 16:54.583
PUT THAT TOGETHER.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

16:54.583 --> 16:56.583
[ ALL MURMURING, GROANING ]

16:59.708 --> 17:01.708
[ BOOK SLAMS ]
OH!

17:01.708 --> 17:03.708
WELCOME TO
THE MORNING MEETING, EVERYBODY.

17:03.708 --> 17:06.458
OR SHOULD I SAY THE "WHENEVER
YOU DECIDE TO SHOW UP" MEETING?

17:06.458 --> 17:09.375
UH, IS THAT
THE OFFICIAL NAME NOW?

17:09.375 --> 17:11.708
'CAUSE THAT WORKS
A LOT BETTER FOR US.

17:11.708 --> 17:12.750
THAT'S RIGHT.
WELL, LISTEN, GUYS,

17:12.750 --> 17:14.708
I AM REALLY
DISAPPOINTED IN YOU,

17:14.708 --> 17:16.125
A-AND, SCOOTER,
YOU'RE FACING THE WRONG WAY.

17:16.125 --> 17:18.708
WHAT?
WHERE -- OH.

17:18.708 --> 17:20.875
YEAH, SORRY.
I LOST MY GLASSES.

17:20.875 --> 17:23.416
THEY CAME OFF WHEN I WAS DOING
"MANIAC" FROM "FLASHDANCE,"

17:23.416 --> 17:25.625
AND I STEPPED ON THEM
LIKE 400 TIMES.

17:25.625 --> 17:28.875
HEY, HEY, HEY. NO, NO, NO.
'CAUSE YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS?

17:28.875 --> 17:30.708
WHAT?
YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS?

17:30.708 --> 17:33.250
GOOD GRIEF.
BUNSEN? BEAKER?

17:33.250 --> 17:35.333
WHY ARE YOU WEARING
EACH OTHER'S CLOTHES?

17:35.333 --> 17:37.458
[ MEEPING ]
[ STAMMERS ]

17:37.458 --> 17:38.708
IF IT HAPPENS
OUTSIDE OF WORK,

17:38.708 --> 17:40.250
WE DON'T OWE HIM
AN EXPLANATION.

17:40.250 --> 17:41.125
OH.

17:41.125 --> 17:42.583
OKAY, LOOK, GUYS.

17:42.583 --> 17:44.583
WE'RE BEHIND NOW, AND WE'RE
REALLY GONNA HAVE TO FOCUS.

17:44.583 --> 17:48.875
HEY, HEY, HEY!
PIGGY NATION REPRESENTING!

17:48.875 --> 17:52.708
[ ALL CHEERING ]
[ LAUGHS ] THAT'S RIGHT.
YOUR QUEEN HAS ARRIVED.

17:52.708 --> 17:54.375
OKAY, OKAY, LOOK.

17:54.375 --> 17:56.958
YOU GUYS ALL HAD YOUR FUN,
BUT NOW IT'S TIME TO WORK.

17:56.958 --> 17:58.291
[ Mockingly ]
"BUT NOW IT'S TIME TO WORK."

17:58.291 --> 17:59.083
[ LAUGHTER ]
WHO SAID THAT?

17:59.083 --> 18:00.708
WHICH ONE OF YOU
SAID THAT?

18:00.708 --> 18:02.083
[ MUTTERS ]

18:02.083 --> 18:04.083
OKAY, HERE'S THE DEAL.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.083
WE'RE GONNA BUCKLE DOWN,
GET THROUGH TODAY,

18:06.083 --> 18:08.250
AND I NEVER WANT THIS
TO HAPPEN AGAIN.

18:08.250 --> 18:10.625
OH, THAT REMINDS ME,
TONIGHT AFTER THE SHOW,

18:10.625 --> 18:11.833
WE<i>ARE </i>GOING OUT AGAIN

18:11.833 --> 18:14.958
BECAUSE I LINED UP A PARTY
WITH USHER!

18:14.958 --> 18:17.958
[ ALL CHEERING ]

18:17.958 --> 18:20.375
NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO, NO!

18:20.375 --> 18:22.458
NO LATE NIGHTS
AND NO USHER!

18:22.458 --> 18:24.708
UH, HELLO?
MY NAME IS FUN.

18:24.708 --> 18:26.208
IS THIS WHERE I COME
TO BE MURDERED?

18:26.208 --> 18:28.500
[ LAUGHTER ]

18:28.500 --> 18:31.166
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S IT.
SHE GOT HIM.

18:31.166 --> 18:33.083
YOU CAN'T KEEP THE CREW OUT
ALL NIGHT, PIGGY.

18:33.083 --> 18:33.958
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S SCREWING UP
THE SHOW.

18:33.958 --> 18:35.208
YOU'RE JUST JEALOUS.

18:35.208 --> 18:36.958
[ SIGHS ]
YOU -- YOU KNOW WHAT YOU NEED?

18:36.958 --> 18:39.250
A GROUP OF FRIENDS
TO HANG OUT WITH AFTER WORK.

18:39.250 --> 18:42.458
I HAVE ONE, AND LET ME TELL YOU,
IT'S DELIGHTFUL.

18:42.458 --> 18:45.708
OKAY. OKAY.

18:45.708 --> 18:47.333
UM...

18:47.333 --> 18:49.208
[ SIGHS ]

18:49.208 --> 18:50.958
Y-YOU KNOW, PIGGY,

18:50.958 --> 18:53.458
I-I-I DIDN'T WANT TO HAVE TO
COME OUT AND SAY IT, BUT...
[ GROANS ]

18:53.458 --> 18:56.375
...BUT WHAT'S REALLY
GOING ON HERE IS THAT, UM,

18:56.375 --> 18:57.708
YOU'RE TOO SPECIAL.

18:57.708 --> 18:59.000
EXACTLY.

18:59.000 --> 19:00.833
WAIT.
UH, TOO SPECIAL FOR WHAT?

19:00.833 --> 19:03.000
UH, TO -- TO HANG OUT
WITH THE CREW, YOU KNOW?

19:03.000 --> 19:05.125
Y-Y-YOU'RE
A GLAMOROUS ICON, PIGGY.

19:05.125 --> 19:07.625
THAT MAY BE MY FAVORITE THING
YOU HAVE EVER SAID.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:07.625 --> 19:09.250
TRY TO TOP IT.

19:09.250 --> 19:12.291
UH, Y-Y-YOU'RE AN IDEAL THAT
THEY SHOULD BE REACHING FOR.

19:12.291 --> 19:13.833
MM.
UH, SO --

19:13.833 --> 19:16.000
SO REALLY
WHAT'S BEST FOR THEM IS TO, UH,

19:16.000 --> 19:17.166
YOU KNOW,
SEE THAT YOU'RE UNAPPROACHABLE.

19:17.166 --> 19:19.833
YES.
LIKE --
LIKE THE STARS IN THE SKY.

19:19.833 --> 19:22.583
YOU ARE MEANT TO BE ADMIRED
FROM A DISTANCE.

19:22.583 --> 19:23.583
[ GASPS ] AWW.

19:23.583 --> 19:25.250
THANK YOU, KERMIT,
FOR --

19:25.250 --> 19:28.416
FOR ACKNOWLEDGING
JUST HOW FABULOUS I AM.

19:28.416 --> 19:32.000
UH, SO, UM, SO YOU'RE GONNA GO
TALK TO THE CREW NOW?

19:32.000 --> 19:36.458
OH. OH, YES, YES.
BUT I DO FEEL BAD FOR THEM.

19:36.458 --> 19:40.000
HMM?
NO, WAIT, I ENVY THEM.

19:40.000 --> 19:41.416
OH.
[ SIGHS ]

19:41.416 --> 19:42.875
WHAT I WOULD GIVE
TO KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE

19:42.875 --> 19:47.458
TO LOOK UP
AND SEE ME FROM BELOW.

19:47.458 --> 19:49.083
MM.
[ SIGHS ]

19:49.083 --> 19:50.625
YOU KNOW, I TRY TO BE
A STAND-UP FROG,

19:50.625 --> 19:53.708
BUT WHEN OUR SHOW'S ON THE LINE,
I CAN MANIPULATE WITH THE BEST.

19:53.708 --> 19:55.708
'CAUSE I LEARNED FROM THE BEST.

19:55.708 --> 19:57.375
[ SIGHS ]

19:57.375 --> 19:59.583
PIGGY REALLY IS THE BEST,
ISN'T SHE?

19:59.583 --> 20:01.875
CAN I HAVE EVERYBODY'S
ATTENTION, PLEASE?
HMM?

20:01.875 --> 20:03.958
FRIENDS,
FOR YOUR OWN GOOD

20:03.958 --> 20:05.708
AND REASONS
YOU'LL NEVER UNDERSTAND,

20:05.708 --> 20:07.375
WE CAN NO LONGER
HANG OUT.

20:07.375 --> 20:09.458
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
EXACTLY.

20:09.458 --> 20:11.708
UNFORTUNATELY, OUR FRIENDSHIP
WILL HAVE TO BE CONDUCTED

20:11.708 --> 20:14.000
FROM A RESPECTABLE
DISTANCE.

20:14.000 --> 20:15.750
BUT WHAT ABOUT
GOING TO USHER'S?

20:15.750 --> 20:17.500
I BOUGHT
A LEATHER SUIT.
WELL, DON'T WORRY.

20:17.500 --> 20:21.958
I WILL BE THERE HAVING
A WONDERFUL TIME WITHOUT YOU.

20:21.958 --> 20:23.583
YOU'RE WELCOME.

20:23.583 --> 20:25.458
[ ALL MURMURING ]

20:25.458 --> 20:26.583
OH, FIDDLE.

20:26.583 --> 20:28.416
AW, GEE WHILLIKERS.

20:28.416 --> 20:29.875
SORRY, GUYS.

20:29.875 --> 20:31.625
UH, I KNOW
YOU'RE ALL DISAPPOINTED,

20:31.625 --> 20:34.000
BUT WHAT CAN I SAY?

20:34.000 --> 20:37.000
I'LL NEVER KNOW
HOW PIGGY'S BRAIN WORKS.

20:37.000 --> 20:39.125
[ SIGHS ]

20:39.125 --> 20:40.333
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:42.708 --> 20:44.083
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

20:44.083 --> 20:46.583
WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM ANYHOW,
HUH?

20:46.583 --> 20:48.000
WELL, HERE THEY ARE
ALPHABETICALLY --

20:48.000 --> 20:49.958
ABSCESSES,
BUNIONS, CONSTIPA--

20:49.958 --> 20:51.750
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.

20:51.750 --> 20:54.333
AND, YEAH, I'M A SUCKER.
MM.

20:54.333 --> 20:55.958
I'M A SUCKER FOR TRYING
TO BE NICE TO YOU.

20:57.458 --> 20:59.166
UGH.

20:59.166 --> 21:01.291
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I WENT TOO FAR.

21:01.291 --> 21:02.833
HOW ABOUT
AFTER THE SHOW,

21:02.833 --> 21:05.958
WALDORF AND I BUY YOU DINNER
AT MUSSO AND FRANK'S?

21:05.958 --> 21:07.750
SURE, THAT --
THAT -- THAT SOUNDS NICE.

21:07.750 --> 21:10.125
ALL RIGHT, THEN, IT'S A DATE.
UH, WE'LL MEET YOU THERE.

21:10.125 --> 21:12.458
OKAY. [ CHUCKLES ]
LOOKING FORWARD TO IT.

21:12.458 --> 21:14.000
YOU GOT IT.

21:14.000 --> 21:15.750
[ LAUGHS ]

21:15.750 --> 21:16.958
I THOUGHT
WE WERE GOING TO DAN TANA'S.

21:16.958 --> 21:18.208
WE ARE.

21:18.208 --> 21:20.000
BUT FIRST I GOT TO STOP BY
MUSSO AND FRANK'S

21:20.000 --> 21:22.166
AND DROP OFF
A SUCKER SIGN.

21:22.166 --> 21:23.125
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
